#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""eid-stack: install/update/list/uninstall the DITEC eID signing stack on Linux.

Components:
  muvm-service  Persistent muvm microVM systemd user service + slim wrappers
                + ~/.local/bin/muvm-guest symlink so PATH lookup finds our build
  dlauncher     D.Launcher 2 (+ dBridge2Nm NM host + Brave/Chrome NM manifest)
  eid-klient    Slovak eID Klient middleware (needs sudo, installs to /usr/lib/)
  dsigner       Pre-fetch D.Signer Java + Zulu JRE 21 (auto-fetched otherwise)
  websigner     Disig WebSigner: fetch/extract its amd64 .deb (no arm64 build
                exists; its own updater can't run here) + re-point through muvm
                — tray autostart, menu entry, browser native-messaging hosts

Commands:
  install   [comp...]   install component(s); default: all
  update    [comp...]   re-download if upstream changed; default: all installed
  reinstall [comp...]   uninstall then install
  uninstall [comp...]   remove component(s); default: all
  list                  show installed versions and update availability
  deps      [install]   check (or install) prerequisites: FEX, FEX RootFS,
                        libkrun(fw), the muvm fork, socat, cargo, dpkg-deb
  help                  show this message

State is tracked in ~/.config/eid-stack/state.json (ETag/Last-Modified per
download, install timestamps). Wrapper scripts at ~/bin/dBridge2Nm.sh and
~/bin/eID_Client.sh are written by this tool.

Requires (see `eid-stack deps`): a muvm fork build, FEX + an x86_64 FEX RootFS,
libkrun/libkrunfw, socat; sudo for eid-klient/websigner and `deps install`.
"""

